---
name: bread pudding
what:
  stale bread - buttered: 7 to 9 pieces
  bread covering:
    eggs: 2 p
    sugar: 1 c
    evaporated milk: 1 can
    water: 1.5 c
    vanilla: 1 t
  sauce:
    butter: 1 stick
    brown sugar: 0.33 c
    flour: 1.5 T
    milk: 0.5 c
    vanilla: 1 t
how:
  - "
  1. Preheat oven to 350°F / 175°C
  \n1. Cut the bread into bite-sized pieces and place in a casserole dish. Whisk together remaining ingredients. Pour the mixture over the bread and allow to absorb. Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
  \n1. For the sauce, stir the butter, flour, brown sugar, milk and vanilla together until the mixture thickens.
  \n1. Let the pudding fall slightly after removing from the oven and pour the sauce over the top.
  "
